This presidential memorandum, issued on March 28, 2020, addresses the need for federal support in response to the COVID-19 pandemic. The memorandum states that it is the policy of the United States to assist state governors in their responses to threats and hazards to the American people. It recognizes the public health risks posed by COVID-19 and the need for cooperation between the federal government and the states. The memorandum directs the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) to fund 100% of emergency assistance activities undertaken by the National Guard forces of Florida, Louisiana, Maryland, Massachusetts, Guam, and Puerto Rico. It also directs the Secretary of Defense to request that the governors of these states and territories order National Guard forces to perform duty on a fully reimbursable basis to support their emergency assistance efforts. The memorandum further states that the 100% federal cost share provided will terminate 30 days from the date of the memorandum. The memorandum concludes with general provisions regarding its implementation.